How and when to use AutoSUM in excel?    
ANS - On top right cormer can see sigma symbol, which shows aggregate function like sum, min, max, avg etc, 
eg if a row has set of numbers to add, from c2 to g2, slect cell next to g2 ie h2 click the autosum and press enter to get the total.
shortcut for autosum
Alt + =
how to get rid of the formula that omits adjacent cell?
Open Excel and then click on File.
Go to Options and then select Formulas.
Look for Error checking rules and uncheck Formulas which omit cells in a region.
Click OK.
How do you select non adjacent cells in Excel 2016?
by holding ctrl key and selecting non adjacent cells or range.
What happens if you choose a column, hold down the Alt key and press the letters
ocw in quick succession? 
the content of the first cell in  selected column will turn to OCW
If you right-click on a row reference number and click on Insert, where will the row
be added? just above that row
